race.comment: THIEM (3) showed good early dash at the first run after a spell last time out and led for most of the way before being claimed and finishing 1.75 lengths away in third over 1100m at Murwillumbah. Well-placed and will take catching. MISHANI SUSPECT (7) has a moderate winning strike-rate but did a good job when returning from a break last time at Dalby, finishing third and only 2 lengths from the winner at the end of 1200m when she did her best work late. Has the class to take this out. LOMBARDI LASS (6) missed the placings when resuming two runs back then didn't do any better last start when 8 lengths away in eighth over 1000m at Sunshine Coast. Capable of featuring prominently. KACHINA GIRL (12) started this preparation with a win then was not as effective last time out when sixth over 1400m at Dalby, beaten 8 lengths. Worth another chance.
